<title>CZECH REPUBLIC: Czech Q1 ave gross wage rises 13.8 percent yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Czech Q1 ave gross wage rises 13.8 percent yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>PRAGUE 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>The average gross nominal wage in the Czech Republic for the first quarter rose 13.8 percent, year-on-year, to 9,385 crowns, the Czech Statistical Bureau (CSU) said on Friday.</p>
<p>Comparative figures were not immediately available.  </p>
<p>The CSU said in a statement that average wages in the private sector for the first three months of the year were 14.1 percent higher at 9,649 crowns, while public sector pay packets rose 12.2 percent to 8,463 crowns.</p>
<p>-- Alan Crosby, Prague Newsroom, 420-2-2423-0003</p>
